Commands to install & start the laravel server:

1) In VS Code. Go to Terminal -> New Terminal
2) Type 'cd my-website'
3) Type composer install
4) Type cp .env.example .env
5) Type php artisan key:generate
6) Type php artisan serve
7) Go to http://127.0.0.1:8000/ in browser

To stop server from running, press ctrl+c

How to make a new controller
(A controller is where you put all the PHP code for loading a webpage)
1) Command "php artisan make:controller {controller name here}"
